`server.js` — API + persistence + import/export/store normalization; **`module.exports = { normalizeStore }`** when required (tests); **`if (require.main === module)`** wraps listen + Discord reminder interval (so `npm test` does not bind a port or start the timer).
- `135` `normalizeEntry(row)` — entry shape, `choreId`, `locationIds`.
- `163` `normalizeChorePreset(row)` — validates title/points/color/scoringMode.
- `178` `normalizeChorePresets(arr)` — array normalization for presets.
- `188` `normalizeQuickChoreIds(ids, presets)` — validates quick bar ids against presets.
- `291` `normalizeStore(raw)` — canonicalizes store object read from disk (`discordWebhook`, `discordReminderSentAt`, **`auditLog`**).
- `GET /api/audit` — recent audit events (auth required); **`appendAudit`** on entry/settings/scheduled/import/discord user actions.
- `451` `app.get('/api/entries', ...)` — list entries + `discordWebhook` for settings UI.
- Discord / Slack / generic webhooks: `POST /api/discord-webhook/test`, `POST /api/discord-webhook/remind-now`; background timer sends overdue reminders per `discordReminderSentAt`; **quiet hours** skip sends; `discordWebhook` holds `quietHours*`, `slackWebhookUrl`, `genericWebhookUrl`.
- `469`–`542` scheduled chore routes; `PUT /api/scheduled-chores/:id` supports title/interval/**startsOn**/**reminderEnabled** updates; `542` `POST .../complete` writes completion entry.
- `588` `app.put('/api/settings', ...)` — settings write (people/presets/quick ids/locations/**discordWebhook** with quiet hours + extra webhook URLs).
- `657` `app.post('/api/import', ...)` — import handler (replace/merge modes).
- `634` `app.get('/api/export', ...)` — export.
- `768` `app.post('/api/entries', ...)` — add entry (supports `choreId`, locations).
- `830` `app.put('/api/entries/:id', ...)` — update entry.

`index.html` — app shell, dialogs, script bootstrap.
- Settings: **Audit log** (`#auditLogList`, …); **Integrations** tab — **Discord reminders** + quiet hours + Slack/generic URLs (`#discordWebhookEnabled`, `#discordWebhookUrl`, `#discordReminderInterval`, `#discordQuietHours*`, `#slackWebhookUrl`, `#genericWebhookUrl`, test / post-now); **nav** (`#settingsNav`, tab panels).
- `62`–`74` **analytics filters** `#analyticsPersonFilter`, `#analyticsLocationFilter`, hint `#analyticsFilterHint`; then `analytics-stats-row` / `statsGrid`, `statsGridPoints`.
- `76`–`94` `section-pair`: contributions (`barsArea`, `barsAreaPoints`) + heatmap `taskHeatmap`.
- `114`–`145` log form: `inChore`, `#scheduledLogSuggestionsWrap` / `#scheduledLogSuggestions` (due soon / overdue, preset title match), `inLocations`, quick log.
- `147`+ `log-mom-row`: **log filter** `#logSearch`, `#logList`, `momGrid`, `momGridPoints`.
- (approx.) `<script type="module" src="/js/chore-tracker.js">` at end of body.

`js/chore-tracker.js` — thin entrypoint → `main.js`.

`js/main.js` — event wiring, auth/bootstrap, mutations, import/export UI flows.
- `205` `load()` — fetch entries/settings, populate state.
- `295` `addEntry()` — main add flow; semicolon payload, posts `/api/entries`.
- `fillChoreFromPreset(presetId)` — sets `#inChore` + per-location locations (shared with quick log).
- `quickLogChore(presetId)` — `fillChoreFromPreset` then `addEntry()`.
- `initScheduledLogSuggestions()` — delegated click on `#scheduledLogSuggestions` → fill + focus chore field.
- `saveScheduledStartDate(id, domKey)` — updates scheduled chore `startsOn` from manage-list date input.
- `setScheduledReminderEnabled` — toggles per-chore **`reminderEnabled`** via `PUT /api/scheduled-chores/:id`.
- Settings shell — **`initSettingsShell`**, **`setSettingsTab`**, sessionStorage tab key; mobile nav toggle + backdrop for `#settingsNav`.
- `524` `startApp()` — init date field, load, pick month, `render()`.
- `534` `bootstrap()` — session check + app/login visibility.
- `#monthSelect` → `switchMonth` (clears log search only).
- `#analyticsPersonFilter` / `#analyticsLocationFilter` `change` → `app.analyticsPersonFilter` / `app.analyticsLocationFilter`, `render()`.
- `#logSearch` `input` → `app.logSearchQuery`, `render()`.
- export/import handlers (`/api/export`, `/api/import`).
- `initQuickChores()`; `initScheduledLogSuggestions()`; chore suggest init nearby.

`js/presets.js` — chore presets + quick log editor + payload resolution.
- `6` `syncChoreDatalists()` — syncs edit dialog datalist.
- `16` `entryChorePoints(e)` — points from preset + per_location × locations.
- `presetMatchingScheduledTitle(title)` — preset match for scheduled log suggestions (exact, then small Levenshtein budget).
- `27` `resolveChorePayloadRows(raw)` — splits `;` and resolves preset ids.
- `43` `saveChorePresetsAndQuick()` — persists settings to `/api/settings`.
- preset/quick editors + `renderQuickChores`.

`js/chore-input-suggest.js` — custom suggestion list for `#inChore`.
- `initChoreInputSuggest()` — keyboard/mouse + segment-aware filtering.

`js/render.js` — render pipeline for dashboard/log/scheduled views.
- `14` `entryMatchesAnalyticsFilters` / `entriesForAnalyticsMonth` — person + location filters for stats/bars/heatmap/MoM (location = entry `locationIds` includes selected name).
- `entryMatchesLogSearch` — log-only text filter (whitespace AND tokens).
- `countsByPerson` / `pointsByPerson` / `taskCountsByDay` — use `entriesForAnalyticsMonth`.
- `fullRender()` — analytics filters, dual stat grids, bars, heatmap, log list, **scheduled log suggestion buttons** (`scheduledStatus` overdue/today/soon + `presetMatchingScheduledTitle`), dual MoM, scheduled dashboard.
- `switchMonth` — sets `app.currentMonth`, clears `app.logSearchQuery`, `render()`.
- `setRenderRenderer(fullRender)` registration.

`js/state.js` — shared mutable app state (`app.entries`, `app.currentMonth`, `app.logSearchQuery`, **`app.analyticsPersonFilter`**, **`app.analyticsLocationFilter`**, …).

`js/render-registry.js` — indirection to avoid import cycles.

`js/scheduled-logic.js` — `scheduledStatus(s)` (overdue / today / soon ≤3 days / later); `intervalLabel`.

`js/utils/date.js` — date helpers and month keys.

`js/api-fetch.js` — fetch wrapper with auth redirect behavior.

`css/chore-tracker-base.css` — reset/theme/shell, top bar, settings dialog, toast.
- `:root` includes `--layout-max-width` (820px; widens at `1100px` / `1440px`).
- `.wrap` uses `var(--layout-max-width)`.

`css/chore-tracker-dashboard.css` — **`.analytics-filters`**, stats, sections, heatmap, bars, MoM, desktop side-by-side rows.

`css/chore-tracker-forms.css` — log form, edit dialog, **`.log-filter-row` / `.log-search-input`**, `.log-list` height (taller at `1100px` + `log-mom-row`).

`css/chore-tracker-scheduled.css` — scheduled dashboard + dialogs + start-date editor (`.scheduled-start-edit`) + **`.scheduled-log-suggestions`** / `.scheduled-suggest-btn`.

`css/chore-tracker-auth.css` — login screen visibility and card.

`css/chore-tracker-extras.css` — chore suggest, preset editors, `#inLocations`, `.log-chore-points`.

`data/chores.json` — persisted store (`entries`, `people`, `chorePresets`, `quickChoreIds`, `locations`, `scheduledChores`, …).

---

## Analytics filters (client-only)

- State: `app.analyticsPersonFilter` (empty = all), `app.analyticsLocationFilter` (empty = all). Not cleared on month change.
- UI: `#analyticsPersonFilter`, `#analyticsLocationFilter`, `#analyticsFilterHint` above the stat grids.
- Scope: task + points stats, contribution bars, daily heatmap, month-over-month (current vs previous month both use the same filters). **Does not** change the activity log (`#logList`); use log search there.
- Location: an entry matches only if `locationIds` includes the selected location (entries with no locations excluded when a location is selected).

## Log search / filter (client-only)

- State: `app.logSearchQuery` (string). Cleared when the month dropdown changes (`switchMonth`).
- UI: `#logSearch` under “Log for …”; styles in `chore-tracker-forms.css`.
- Matching: `entryMatchesLogSearch` — whitespace tokens AND; haystack = date, chore, person, locations, points. Only affects `#logList`.

## Scheduled log suggestions (client-only)

- Shown when a scheduled chore is **overdue**, **due today**, or **due within 3 days** (`scheduledStatus` `soon`), and its **title matches a chore preset** (exact case-insensitive, or close fuzzy match via `presetMatchingScheduledTitle` — e.g. “Wipe …” vs “Wiped …”).
- Renders under “Log a chore”, above Quick log. Tap fills `#inChore` (and per-location selects like quick log); user picks person/date and **Add**. Does **not** call scheduled “complete” API — use Scheduled dashboard **Mark done** to reset the timer.

---

## Feature map

### Auth and server

- **Login** — `POST /api/login` with env `CHORELOG_USER` / `CHORELOG_PASSWORD` (defaults documented in code); **logout** `POST /api/logout`.
- **Brute-force protection** — failed sign-ins are tracked **per client IP** (`lib/login-throttle.cjs`); after `CHORELOG_LOGIN_MAX_FAILURES` (default 8) failures within `CHORELOG_LOGIN_WINDOW_MS` (default 15 min), the IP is locked out for `CHORELOG_LOGIN_LOCKOUT_MS` (default 15 min). State in **`data/login-throttle.json`** (survives restarts). **`429`** with `Retry-After` and JSON `{ error, retryAfterSeconds }` when locked out. **`CHORELOG_TRUST_PROXY=1`** sets Express `trust proxy` so `req.ip` reflects `X-Forwarded-For` behind a reverse proxy.
- **Session** — signed HMAC cookie (`chorelog_auth`) includes **`user`** (username) for audit actor; ~30-day expiry; secret from `CHORELOG_SECRET` (dev default in code). **`GET /api/auth`** returns `{ authenticated, user }` when valid.
- **API guard** — all `/api/*` except auth/version/login require a valid cookie (`requireApiAuth` sets `req.authPayload`).
- **Persistence** — default: JSON file **`data/chores.json`**; **atomic write** (temp + rename). **Optional SQLite**: set **`CHORELOG_SQLITE_PATH`** — bare filename (e.g. `chores.db`) → **`data/chores.db`**; paths starting with **`data/`** (e.g. `./data/chores.db`) → from **project root**; absolute paths as-is. Parent dirs are created if missing. Uses Node built-in **`node:sqlite`** (`DatabaseSync`, WAL). If the DB has no row yet, the server **one-time imports** existing `data/chores.json` then serves from SQLite. **`ensureSeed`** unchanged (demo rows if empty).
- **Version** — **`GET /api/version`** returns `version`, `nodeVersion`, `persistence` (`json`|`sqlite`), `databaseRelativePath`, optional `sqliteVersion` / `journalMode`, `exportSchemaVersion` (matches export JSON `version`); footer + Settings **About** tab.

### Data model (store)

- **Entries** — `d`, `c`, `p`, optional `choreId`, `locationIds`, `createdAt` / `updatedAt`.
- **People & locations** — editable lists; at least one each enforced in UI.
- **Chore presets** — `title`, `points` (clamped), hex `color`, `scoringMode` `flat` | **`per_location`**.
- **Quick bar** — up to **24** preset ids validated against presets.
- **Scheduled chores** — `intervalDays`, `startsOn`, `lastCompletedAt`, **`reminderEnabled`** (omit or true = include in overdue webhook reminders), timestamps; next due from last completion or start date.
- **`discordWebhook`** — `enabled`, `url` (Discord), `reminderIntervalMinutes`, **`quietHoursEnabled`**, **`quietHoursStart`/`End`** (server local `HH:MM`), **`slackWebhookUrl`** (`hooks.slack.com`), **`genericWebhookUrl`** (HTTPS, Discord-shaped JSON); see `normalizeDiscordWebhook` in `server.js`.
- **Audit log** — `auditLog[]` (`id`, `at`, `actor`, `action`, `target`, optional `detail`); newest first; capped (e.g. 500); one household store = one audit stream.

### Chore logging

- **Main form** — date, person, chore text, multi-select locations (for `per_location` presets).
- **Semicolon bundles** — `;` separates multiple preset/title segments in one submit; server/client resolve rows (`resolveChorePayloadRows`).
- **Preset resolution** — optional `choreId` + free-text `c`; points from preset + locations when applicable.
- **Quick log** — one tap from bar; **`fillChoreFromPreset`** sets chore field + locations when none selected for per-location presets.
- **Custom suggestions** — `chore-input-suggest.js`: preset picker **per segment** (query after last `;`), keyboard/mouse, color stripe from preset; avoids whole-field `<datalist>` matching.
- **Add toast** — success message + **Undo** (removes last created entries via API).

### Activity log (month-scoped)

- **List** — current **month** only (from month selector); sorted by date descending.
- **Row UI** — date, chore text, person chip; **preset color** left border when `choreId` set; **+N pts** and **location names** when present.
- **Edit** — dialog with date, chore (datalist), person, locations; **`PUT /api/entries/:id`**.
- **Delete** — confirm dialog; **`DELETE /api/entries/:id`**.
- **Log search** — client-only AND-of-tokens across date/chore/person/locations/points; cleared on month change.

### Analytics and dashboard

- **Month picker** — options from distinct entry months (newest first); drives all dashboard + log views.
- **Dual metrics** — **task counts** vs **preset points** (parallel stat cards, bars, MoM columns).
- **Stat cards** — totals, most active / top earner, active days, members with activity, **balance %** (fairness across people), avg points per task (points grid).
- **Contribution bars** — per-person horizontal bars for tasks and points (separate max scaling).
- **Heatmap** — tasks per calendar day in selected month; intensity vs busiest day; weekday header; “busiest day” footer; respects analytics filters.
- **Analytics filters** — **person** and **location** (entry must include location when filtered); apply to stats, bars, heatmap, MoM — **not** the activity log.
- **Month-over-month** — previous month vs current for tasks and points; **% change** with up/down styling; handles “no previous month”.

### Scheduled chores

- **Intervals** — day, week, 2–3 weeks, ~month, 2–3 months (stored as `intervalDays`).
- **Due logic** — overdue / today / soon (≤3 days) / later (`scheduled-logic.js`); human-readable next due.
- **Main dashboard strip** — cards with status + **Mark done**; section **hidden** when there are no scheduled chores.
- **Manage dialog** — add (title + interval), list with **start date** edits, **per-chore “Remind when overdue (webhooks)”** checkbox (`reminderEnabled`), remove; **`PUT`/`DELETE`** routes.
- **Mark done flow** — dialog picks person; **`POST .../complete`** adds log line with scheduled title and resets timer; optional **`completedDate`** (calendar day).
- **Overdue reminders** — optional **Discord**, **Slack** (`hooks.slack.com`), and/or **generic HTTPS** URLs (same payload as Discord where applicable); **quiet hours** (server local clock, can span midnight); per-chore **`reminderEnabled`**; **server timer** + min interval per chore (`discordReminderSentAt`); **test** and **post overdue now** endpoints.
- **Log-form suggestions** — buttons for urgent scheduled titles that **match a preset** (exact/fuzzy); fill chore + locations only; does not complete scheduled item (use Mark done for timer).

### Settings and data lifecycle

- **Settings layout** — tabbed **nav** (`#settingsNav`, categories: Interface, Household, Chores, Integrations, Account, Audit, Data, **About**); **About** loads **`GET /api/version`** (app version, Node, storage type, data file path, SQLite engine + journal mode when applicable, export schema version); scrollable **panel** content; hamburger + backdrop on small viewports; last tab in `sessionStorage` (`chorelog-settings-tab`).
- **Integrations** — overdue webhook reminders: Discord URL, reminder interval, **quiet hours**, optional **Slack** + **generic HTTPS** URLs; Save / Send test / Post overdue now (`js/main.js` + `server.js` as above).
- **Appearance** — theme **system / light / dark** (`localStorage` + inline head script to prevent flash); **`syncThemeMeta`** for `theme-color`.
- **People / locations / presets / quick bar** — CRUD in UI; **`PUT /api/settings`** batches updates.
- **Export** — **`GET /api/export`** (full JSON backup) and **`GET /api/export/entries.csv`** (log rows only, UTF-8 BOM, RFC 4180-style quoting); Settings → Data **Export JSON** / **Export CSV**.
- **Import** — file upload; **replace** or **merge** with confirmation; backup may include **`auditLog`** (export v5).
- **Audit log UI** — Settings → load **`GET /api/audit`** on open + Refresh; shows actor (signed-in account) and action summaries.
- **PWA** — `site.webmanifest` (standalone, icons); **`sw.js`** — installability hook, **no caching** of `/api` (see file comment); Apple touch icon / meta tags.

### Client infrastructure

- **`api-fetch.js`** — shared fetch behavior (e.g. auth failures).
- **Render registry** — breaks import cycles between render and main.
- **Responsive shell** — `--layout-max-width` steps at ~820px / 1100px / 1440px; log + MoM side-by-side on wide layouts.
- **i18n** — `localStorage` key `chorelog-locale` (`en` | `de`); nested JSON flattened to dotted keys; `t(key, vars)`; `initI18n()` in `chore-tracker.js` before `main.js`; Settings → Language; month names and dates use `getLocaleBcp47()` (`en-US` / `de-DE`).
- **Automated tests** — `npm test` runs **`node --test`** on `test/*.test.cjs`: `normalizeStore` (via `module.exports` from `server.js`, no listen/timer when required), **next due** math (mirrors `js/utils/date.js`), **semicolon resolve** rules (mirrors `resolveChorePayloadRows`). GitHub Actions: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` on push/PR to `main`/`master`. Further ideas: HTTP import-merge, `scheduledStatus` labels with i18n stubs.

## Future ideas (implementation-oriented)

- **Soft delete** or archive for presets and log rows.
- **Fuzzy / typo-tolerant** matching for each `;` segment in the chore field (beyond current suggest list).
- **Backup snapshots** — timestamped copy of `chores.json` before destructive import or on a schedule.
- **True offline mode** — cache static assets + read-only queue in SW; conflict rules for writes.
- **Push notifications** (PWA) as an alternative to Discord for mobile users.
- **Calendar-native recurrence** — e.g. “every second Tuesday” vs fixed day intervals only.
- ~~**CSV / spreadsheet export** for entries.~~ **Done** — `GET /api/export/entries.csv`, Settings → **Export CSV**.
- **Multi-household or multi-user** accounts with isolated stores.
- **Read-only or guest** role (view stats, no edit).
- **Tags or categories** orthogonal to presets.
- **Streaks / goals** — weekly targets, gentle nudges in UI.
- **Attachments** — optional photo per log entry (storage + privacy policy).
- **More locales** — extend `locales/*.json` and `SUPPORTED_LOCALES` in `js/i18n.js`.
- **OpenAPI** or short route doc generated from `server.js` for integrators.
- **Helm chart** or raw Kubernetes manifests for multi-replica deploys.

